HEADWORD: Postponement
<hw>Post*pone"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
postponing; a deferring, or putting off, to a future time; a temporary
delay.</def> <rj><au>Macaulay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Postponence</ent>⟦br⟧
